#: ../../../networking/device_drivers/ethernet/freescale/dpaa2/overview.rst:81
msgid "DPRC (Datapath Resource Container)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/device_drivers/ethernet/freescale/dpaa2/overview.rst:83
msgid ""
"A DPRC is a container object that holds all the other types of DPAA2 "
"objects.  In the example diagram below there are 8 objects of 5 types "
"(DPMCP, DPIO, DPBP, DPNI, and DPMAC) in the container."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/device_drivers/ethernet/freescale/dpaa2/overview.rst:103
msgid ""
"From the point of view of an OS, a DPRC behaves similar to a plug and play "
"bus, like PCI.  DPRC commands can be used to enumerate the contents of the "
"DPRC, discover the hardware objects present (including mappable regions and "
"interrupts)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/device_drivers/ethernet/freescale/dpaa2/overview.rst:118
msgid ""
"Hardware objects can be created and destroyed dynamically, providing the "
"ability to hot plug/unplug objects in and out of the DPRC."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/device_drivers/ethernet/freescale/dpaa2/overview.rst:121
msgid ""
"A DPRC has a mappable MMIO region (an MC portal) that can be used to send MC "
"commands.  It has an interrupt for status events (like hotplug). All objects "
"in a container share the same hardware \"isolation context\". This means "
"that with respect to an IOMMU the isolation granularity is at the DPRC "
"(container) level, not at the individual object level."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/device_drivers/ethernet/freescale/dpaa2/overview.rst:129
msgid ""
"DPRCs can be defined statically and populated with objects via a config file "
"passed to the MC when firmware starts it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/device_drivers/ethernet/freescale/dpaa2/overview.rst:133
msgid "DPAA2 Objects for an Ethernet Network Interface"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/device_drivers/ethernet/freescale/dpaa2/overview.rst:135
msgid ""
"A typical Ethernet NIC is monolithic-- the NIC device contains TX/RX queuing "
"mechanisms, configuration mechanisms, buffer management, physical ports, and "
"interrupts.  DPAA2 uses a more granular approach utilizing multiple hardware "
"objects.  Each object provides specialized functions. Groups of these "
"objects are used by software to provide Ethernet network interface "
"functionality.  This approach provides efficient use of finite hardware "
"resources, flexibility, and performance advantages."
msgstr ""

