#: ../../../networking/device_drivers/ethernet/freescale/dpaa2/overview.rst:398
msgid "MAC driver"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/device_drivers/ethernet/freescale/dpaa2/overview.rst:399
msgid ""
"An Ethernet PHY is an off-chip, board specific component and is managed by "
"the appropriate PHY driver via an mdio bus.  The MAC driver plays a role of "
"being a proxy between the PHY driver and the MC.  It does this proxy via the "
"MC commands to a DPMAC object. If the PHY driver signals a link change, the "
"MAC driver notifies the MC via a DPMAC command.  If a network interface is "
"brought up or down, the MC notifies the DPMAC driver via an interrupt and "
"the driver can take appropriate action."
msgstr ""
